They cry and scream
a silent scream.

00:11:16.325 --> 00:11:17.450
You won't be able to sleep.

00:11:17.450 --> 00:11:18.710
It's horrible.

00:11:18.710 --> 00:11:21.850
Because it messes up the inside.

00:11:21.850 --> 00:11:23.510
The integrity gets
a little bit mealy.

00:11:23.510 --> 00:11:25.586
So you can put them
on the counter,

00:11:25.586 --> 00:11:26.710
not in the direct sunlight.

00:11:26.710 --> 00:11:28.540
But when they're ripe,
that's good to go.

00:11:28.540 --> 00:11:31.454
Or, if you go to your farmer's
market and there's a lot

00:11:31.454 --> 00:11:33.870
of tomatoes, you're like, oh,
$1.00 a pound for heirlooms,

00:11:33.870 --> 00:11:35.260
that's great.

00:11:35.260 --> 00:11:38.430
You can just grab a whole
flat--it's totally worth it--

00:11:38.430 --> 00:11:42.050
get freezer zip bags, put
them all in a freezer zip bag,

00:11:42.050 --> 00:11:44.940
and just put them
in the freezer.

00:11:44.940 --> 00:11:48.210
The reason for that is
because when you can a tomato,

00:11:48.210 --> 00:11:49.480
you're kind of boiling it.

00:11:49.480 --> 00:11:50.670
You're heating it,
so you're canning it.

00:11:50.670 --> 00:11:52.900
So you're actually breaking
down the flavor of that tomato

00:11:52.900 --> 00:11:54.660
by heating it for a
long period of time.

00:11:54.660 --> 00:11:57.860
When you freeze it, it doesn't
break down the flavor at all.

00:11:57.860 --> 00:12:00.410
And then, come winter time,
when you want to make yourself

00:12:00.410 --> 00:12:02.868
like a really delicious grilled
cheese sandwich with tomato

00:12:02.868 --> 00:12:05.720
soup, you just put it
under cold running water,

00:12:05.720 --> 00:12:07.770
and then the frost just
on the inside of the skin

00:12:07.770 --> 00:12:09.960
peels off like a sock.

00:12:09.960 --> 00:12:11.975
And you just throw the
whole thing in your pot.

00:12:11.975 --> 00:12:13.850
It has a lot of flavor
in there, so you don't

00:12:13.850 --> 00:12:15.058
have to actually do anything.

00:12:15.058 --> 00:12:18.140
You can neglect your produce
and have amazing food.

