So I would normally
put this in the fridge,

00:19:23.670 --> 00:19:26.030
let it chill out for a bit.

00:19:26.030 --> 00:19:27.120
Taste it.

00:19:27.120 --> 00:19:29.174
Tasting is also very important.

00:19:31.700 --> 00:19:35.180
If it needs more salt,
decide whether or not

00:19:35.180 --> 00:19:36.710
you want to add a bit more acid.

00:19:36.710 --> 00:19:39.440
So acid will bring out the
natural sodium in food.

00:19:39.440 --> 00:19:41.523
So if you have anybody in
the family, or yourself,

00:19:41.523 --> 00:19:44.172
you're watching how much sodium
you intake, the last little bit

00:19:44.172 --> 00:19:46.130
you're like, hmm, does
it need more brightness,

00:19:46.130 --> 00:19:47.390
or does it need more salt?

00:19:47.390 --> 00:19:48.610
If it needs salt, salt it.

00:19:48.610 --> 00:19:51.880
If it needs brightness, you
can add a little more red wine

00:19:51.880 --> 00:19:54.181
vinegar or lemon juice,
and that will actually

00:19:54.181 --> 00:19:55.430
bring up a little more sodium.

