00:35:51.660 --> 00:35:53.270
So let's not burn them.

00:35:53.270 --> 00:35:56.240
And when they're good,
they're just like so good.

00:35:56.240 --> 00:35:58.595
So I'm going to get some of
these and pop those on top.

00:36:02.880 --> 00:36:04.810
Other than one
allergy to pine nuts,

00:36:04.810 --> 00:36:07.150
does anyone not like pine nuts?

00:36:07.150 --> 00:36:08.461
Great.

00:36:08.461 --> 00:36:09.610
They're all going in there.

00:36:09.610 --> 00:36:10.942
That's fantastic.

00:36:10.942 --> 00:36:12.650
And then what we'll
do is we'll taste it.

00:36:12.650 --> 00:36:16.170
So we have an acid,
which is the lemon juice.

00:36:16.170 --> 00:36:18.830
We also have salt, which
is in the form of salt.

00:36:18.830 --> 00:36:21.201
And then we also have the
cheese, which has salt in it

00:36:21.201 --> 00:36:21.700
also.

00:36:21.700 --> 00:36:23.866
So it's a little bit different
because it's buttery.

00:36:23.866 --> 00:36:26.277
So we'll give it a flavor,
a little flavor test here.

00:36:26.277 --> 00:36:27.610
And then we'll see what happens.

00:36:34.010 --> 00:36:35.240
It's like I made it before.

00:36:35.240 --> 00:36:37.030
This is really-- it's
great, because it

00:36:37.030 --> 00:36:39.830
has a lot of fresh herbs in it.

00:36:39.830 --> 00:36:40.972
Never be afraid of herbs.

00:36:40.972 --> 00:36:43.180
People are like, what do
you do with all those herbs?

00:36:43.180 --> 00:36:44.290
You use them.

00:36:44.290 --> 00:36:46.400
I mean, you just use them.

00:36:46.400 --> 00:36:48.160
And the more herbs, the better.

00:36:48.160 --> 00:36:51.206
It's like when you
have Thai food,

00:36:51.206 --> 00:36:52.830
they just throw so
many herbs on there.

00:36:52.830 --> 00:36:53.770
There's never been
a moment I was

00:36:53.770 --> 00:36:54.850
like, that's a lot of herbs.

00:36:54.850 --> 00:36:56.308
Can you just cut
back on the herbs?

00:36:56.308 --> 00:37:01.600
I've always been very happy with
the volume of herbs in my food.

00:37:01.600 --> 00:37:04.560
And again, you eat
with your eyes.

00:37:04.560 --> 00:37:06.230
Make it really pretty.

00:37:06.230 --> 00:37:10.450
I'm not a-- I'm not
one of those dudes that

00:37:10.450 --> 00:37:13.791
has the tweezer things.

00:37:13.791 --> 00:37:15.790
There's nowhere in my
cookbook this says, go out

00:37:15.790 --> 00:37:19.720
and get a thing of surgical
tweezers to compose your food.

00:37:19.720 --> 00:37:21.650
I'm not saying you
can't, because I've

00:37:21.650 --> 00:37:25.420
seen some beautifully
composed dishes.

00:37:25.420 --> 00:37:27.600
But because I feel that
we're all family now,

00:37:27.600 --> 00:37:31.220
this is all family style.

00:37:31.220 --> 00:37:33.260
And we can all pass
this around here

00:37:33.260 --> 00:37:35.915
at Team Google-- I'm just
coming up with these things

00:37:35.915 --> 00:37:36.540
left and right.

