I'm sure you would tell me if
I had stuff in my teeth, which

00:38:03.600 --> 00:38:04.270
I'm sure I do.

00:38:04.270 --> 00:38:05.740
But thanks for your time.

00:38:05.740 --> 00:38:07.320
Any questions, I'm
ready to take them

00:38:07.320 --> 00:38:11.507
[APPLAUSE]

00:38:11.507 --> 00:38:13.590
JENNA TAYLOR: I have a
question about cauliflower.

00:38:13.590 --> 00:38:14.150
NATHAN LYON: Question.

00:38:14.150 --> 00:38:16.191
JENNA TAYLOR: It's one of
my favorite vegetables.

00:38:16.191 --> 00:38:16.710
I love it.

00:38:16.710 --> 00:38:19.120
But I notice that
sometimes I buy a head,

00:38:19.120 --> 00:38:22.630
and it sits in my fridge, and
it has a terrible strong smell.

00:38:22.630 --> 00:38:24.700
And sometimes it's
completely neutral.

00:38:24.700 --> 00:38:27.070
It doesn't smell like anything,
completely unoffensive.

00:38:27.070 --> 00:38:28.220
What causes that?

00:38:28.220 --> 00:38:29.500
How do I differentiate?

00:38:29.500 --> 00:38:31.090
Does it matter?

00:38:31.090 --> 00:38:33.460
NATHAN LYON: I mean, it's
breaking down, for one.

00:38:33.460 --> 00:38:36.240
It's the same-- I believe
it's the same family as kale.

00:38:36.240 --> 00:38:38.950
Like kale will give
you that same smell.

00:38:41.810 --> 00:38:43.990
If it's constricted
at all-- you want

00:38:43.990 --> 00:38:47.820
to make sure the airflow
happens around it.

00:38:47.820 --> 00:38:49.250
I'm using the
analogy of the kale.

00:38:49.250 --> 00:38:52.470
When you get kale home and
it has that little twisty tie

00:38:52.470 --> 00:38:55.620
and or fresh herbs, you need to
get it out of that twisty tie.

00:38:55.620 --> 00:38:57.200
It doesn't like
to be constrained,

00:38:57.200 --> 00:38:59.700
because when they're
smooshed together like that,

00:38:59.700 --> 00:39:01.940
the leaves or the
herbs, what happens

00:39:01.940 --> 00:39:04.639
is any of that moisture
will actually begin to rot.

00:39:04.639 --> 00:39:05.930
And that's when it breaks down.

00:39:05.930 --> 00:39:06.770
Think of spinach.

00:39:06.770 --> 00:39:08.782
When you get a bag
of spinach, and it's

00:39:08.782 --> 00:39:10.990
been sitting in your fridge
or in your crisper drawer

00:39:10.990 --> 00:39:12.590
that you call like
the death drawer

00:39:12.590 --> 00:39:14.240
or whatever you call,
because right now

00:39:14.240 --> 00:39:15.960
there's a bunch of flaccid
vegetables in your death

00:39:15.960 --> 00:39:16.220
drawer.

00:39:16.220 --> 00:39:17.205
I know it for a fact.

00:39:17.205 --> 00:39:20.664
We could go take a
Google van, I know it.

00:39:20.664 --> 00:39:23.080
It's just because, when you
look at the bottom of the bag,

00:39:23.080 --> 00:39:26.320
you're like, ooh, that's
weird dark spinach juice.

00:39:26.320 --> 00:39:27.780
That's disgusting.

00:39:27.780 --> 00:39:29.420
It's because it can't breathe.

00:39:29.420 --> 00:39:33.350
So if I ever get fresh-- if
I'm traveling doing something,

00:39:33.350 --> 00:39:35.607
and I want a salad, I'll
get the package of salad,

00:39:35.607 --> 00:39:38.190
and I'll poke a bunch of holes
in it and put it in the fridge.

00:39:38.190 --> 00:39:40.372
The holes will
allow it to exhale,

00:39:40.372 --> 00:39:42.330
but it won't dehydrate
hydrate because it's not

00:39:42.330 --> 00:39:43.910
completely exposed.

00:39:43.910 --> 00:39:45.670
So that's why the
crisper drawer is there,

00:39:45.670 --> 00:39:49.090
so it won't dehydrate
it like it would if it's

00:39:49.090 --> 00:39:51.650
on top of just a drawer.

00:39:51.650 --> 00:39:52.779
So it stays cool enough.

00:39:52.779 --> 00:39:54.320
But you need to let
it breathe, also.

00:39:54.320 --> 00:39:55.910
But that's a great question.

00:39:55.910 --> 00:39:57.290
Great question.

00:39:57.290 --> 00:39:57.790
OK.

00:39:57.790 --> 00:40:01.690
The question is, what are my
favorite spices to cook with?

00:40:01.690 --> 00:40:05.202
I think that sort of
depends on the cuisine.

00:40:05.202 --> 00:40:05.910
It's interesting.

00:40:05.910 --> 00:40:08.326
So when you look at spices and
you're thinking, all right,

00:40:08.326 --> 00:40:13.680
well, here's a chili and cumin
and fennel, or definitely

00:40:13.680 --> 00:40:15.100
cumin.

