00:44:50.260 --> 00:44:52.450
it has to be accessible
to the home cook

00:44:52.450 --> 00:44:54.330
regardless where
you get your food,

00:44:54.330 --> 00:44:56.560
be it in the farmers
market in Palo Alto,

00:44:56.560 --> 00:44:58.950
or at-- the majority
of Americans

00:44:58.950 --> 00:45:00.870
get their stuff from Wal Mart.

00:45:00.870 --> 00:45:04.040
And then we'll sometimes also
go to different grocery stores

00:45:04.040 --> 00:45:06.400
to get a particular
product, and then

00:45:06.400 --> 00:45:09.129
design the recipe making
sure that it works with all

00:45:09.129 --> 00:45:11.670
of those different products from
all those different sources,

00:45:11.670 --> 00:45:14.420
