of in the kitchen?

00:45:41.940 --> 00:45:44.720
What do we not
necessarily-- what direction

00:45:44.720 --> 00:45:46.884
have we not gone into?

00:45:46.884 --> 00:45:48.800
That's why when we eat
out, we'll eat out food

00:45:48.800 --> 00:45:50.870
that we're not
necessarily familiar with,

00:45:50.870 --> 00:45:54.560
but you want to educate
America and make

00:45:54.560 --> 00:45:56.320
it accessible for them.

00:45:56.320 --> 00:45:58.880
So my dad hated eggplant.

00:45:58.880 --> 00:46:01.687
He hated eggplant,
or brussels sprouts.

00:46:01.687 --> 00:46:03.270
My mom would just
cook it until it was

00:46:03.270 --> 00:46:05.280
like mushy brussels sprout ass.

00:46:05.280 --> 00:46:07.800
It was horrible, and your
kitchen smelled horrible.

00:46:07.800 --> 00:46:09.300
But then I came to
California, and I

00:46:09.300 --> 00:46:11.830
was like, oh, roasted
brussels sprouts

00:46:11.830 --> 00:46:13.070
with balsamic and shallots.

00:46:13.070 --> 00:46:13.625
So delicious.

00:46:13.625 --> 00:46:15.360
It' crispy, it's sweet.

00:46:15.360 --> 00:46:17.560
It is a vastly different animal.

00:46:17.560 --> 00:46:19.950
So we also try to think
out of the box and say,

00:46:19.950 --> 00:46:21.420
most people eat it this way.

00:46:21.420 --> 00:46:23.110
How do we prepare
it a different way?

00:46:23.110 --> 00:46:25.930
So they're not just bored
with the same old routine of,

00:46:25.930 --> 00:46:28.390
