because I'm tired.

00:46:32.410 --> 00:46:35.119
So how can we reinvent
the cauliflower

00:46:35.119 --> 00:46:36.910
to where you don't just
have to either make

00:46:36.910 --> 00:46:39.310
a puree out of it--
which is delicious--

00:46:39.310 --> 00:46:41.960
throw it in a food processor,
steam it with butter, salt

00:46:41.960 --> 00:46:43.460
and pepper, done.

00:46:43.460 --> 00:46:47.370
Or you can cut into slabs and
throw it in your broiler at 450

00:46:47.370 --> 00:46:50.620
with a lot of spices, and make
these big slabs, or steaks.

00:46:50.620 --> 00:46:51.540
Done.

00:46:51.540 --> 00:46:54.470
So we're trying to say, how do
you utilize the same ingredient

00:46:54.470 --> 00:46:58.210
in a new and exciting way
that perhaps hasn't been done

00:46:58.210 --> 00:47:00.770
before, or sort of
splinter off in a way

00:47:00.770 --> 00:47:03.910
that all Americans will be
like, I can totally do that.

00:47:03.910 --> 00:47:07.010
I have-- except for the young
lady on my left-- I totally

00:47:07.010 --> 00:47:08.717
have this.

00:47:08.717 --> 00:47:10.300
So that's why I
designed the gazpacho.

00:47:10.300 --> 00:47:11.674
Instead of making
people be like,

00:47:11.674 --> 00:47:14.080
oh, you're going to do
this brunoisette of this,

00:47:14.080 --> 00:47:15.538
and people aren't
going to do that.

00:47:15.538 --> 00:47:17.557
But they can go
bzzz, dinner's ready.

00:47:17.557 --> 00:47:19.140
So I hope that
answered your question.

